unemploy = 
  read_csv("Unemployment.csv") %>% 
  separate(label, into = c("year", "month")) %>%
  dplyr::filter(year != 2017)
## Rows: 2900 Columns: 5
## -- Column specification --------------------------------------------------------
## Delimiter: ","
## chr (3): series_id, period, label
## dbl (2): year, value
## 
## i Use `spec()` to retrieve the full column specification for this data.
## i Specify the column types or set `show_col_types = FALSE` to quiet this message.
unemploy = dplyr::rename(unemploy, state = series_id)

gun_violence = 
  read_csv("data/year_month_state_massshooting.csv") %>% 
  mutate(year = year + 2000) %>% 
  mutate(year = as.character(year))
## New names:
## * `` -> ...1
## Rows: 911 Columns: 5
## -- Column specification --------------------------------------------------------
## Delimiter: ","
## chr (2): month, state
## dbl (3): ...1, year, number_mass_shooting
## 
## i Use `spec()` to retrieve the full column specification for this data.
## i Specify the column types or set `show_col_types = FALSE` to quiet this message.
new_dataframe = 
  left_join(unemploy, gun_violence, by = c("state" = "state", "year" = "year", "month" = "month")) %>% 
  select(-...1, -period) %>% 
  mutate(number_mass_shooting = replace(number_mass_shooting, is.na(number_mass_shooting),  0))

illinois = 
  new_dataframe %>% 
  dplyr::filter(state == "Illinois") %>% 
  dplyr::select(number_mass_shooting)

time series analysis for illinois from 2018-2021

time series analysis for illinois from 2018-2019

illinois_1819 = 
  new_dataframe %>% 
  filter(
    year %in% c("2018","2019"),
    state == "Illinois") %>% 
  select(number_mass_shooting)

month.ts1 = ts(illinois_1819, start = 2018, frequency = 12)
plot(decompose(month.ts1, type = "multiplicative"))
plot(month.ts1)
abline(reg=lm(month.ts1 ~ time(month.ts1)))
boxplot(month.ts1 ~ cycle(month.ts1))


trend = lm(month.ts1 ~ c(1:length(month.ts1)))
detrend = residuals(trend)
new_ts = ts(detrend, start = 2018, frequency = 12)
plot.ts(new_ts)

lambda <- BoxCox.lambda(new_ts)
print(lambda)
new_diff_ts = diff(new_ts, lag = 3)
plot.ts(new_diff_ts)
adf.test(new_diff_ts)

par(mfrow = c(1,2))
acf(new_diff_ts)
acf(new_diff_ts, plot = F)
pacf(new_diff_ts)
pacf(new_diff_ts, plot = F)

ets_ts = new_diff_ts %>% ets()
checkresiduals(ets_ts)
new_diff_ts %>% 
  ets() %>% 
  forecast(h = 6) %>% 
  autoplot()
